Calculate the posterior predictive distributions. Helps to check the fitness of the model. Use it in conjunction with the shinystan app to visualize some nice posterior predictive plots

Source: R/bpc_exports.R
posterior_predictive.Rd

Calculate the posterior predictive distributions. Helps to check the fitness of the model. Use it in conjunction with the shinystan app to visualize some nice posterior predictive plots

posterior_predictive(bpc_object, n = 100)

Arguments

bpc_object

a bpc object
n

number of times to sample from the posterior

Value

a list containing two values: y value that represents the collected data and y_pred that represents the predictive posterior matrix

Examples

# \donttest{
m<-bpc(data = tennis_agresti,
player0 = 'player0',
player1 = 'player1',
result_column = 'y',
model_type = 'bt',
solve_ties = 'none')
